#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF'
npm helper commands available in this container
==============================================

npm-help
  Lists the available npm helper commands.

npm-ci-dev
  Installs dependencies from package-lock.json using npm ci.
  Recommended after cloning the project or switching branches.
  Removes node_modules before reinstalling.

npm-install-dev
  Runs npm install.
  Useful when you intentionally changed package.json and want npm to update package-lock.json.

npm-audit
  Runs npm audit.
  Also runs a production-only audit with:
    npm audit --omit=dev

npm-security-check
  Runs a broader dependency/security check:
    - Node version
    - npm version
    - package-lock presence
    - npm ci dry checks where possible
    - npm audit
    - npm audit --omit=dev
    - npm outdated

npm-outdated
  Shows outdated dependencies.

npm-require package[@version]
  Adds a production dependency.
  Example:
    npm-require zod

npm-require-dev package[@version]
  Adds a development dependency.
  Example:
    npm-require-dev eslint

npm-update-safe package [package ...]
  Updates selected packages only.
  Refuses to run a global npm update without package names.
  Example:
    npm-update-safe @angular/core @angular/cli

npm-why-package package
  Explains why a package is installed.
  Internally uses:
    npm explain package

ng
  Runs the local Angular CLI from node_modules/.bin/ng.

Recommended daily workflow
==========================

After cloning the project:
  npm-ci-dev

Before committing dependency changes:
  npm-security-check

Add a production dependency:
  npm-require package

Add a development dependency:
  npm-require-dev package

Update selected packages:
  npm-update-safe package

Check outdated dependencies:
  npm-outdated

Important npm rules
===================

Use npm ci for reproducible installs based on package-lock.json.

Use npm install when you intentionally want to modify package-lock.json.

Avoid global npm update.

Always review changes in:
  package.json
  package-lock.json

For Angular major upgrades, prefer:
  ng update @angular/core @angular/cli
EOF
